Master Answer:
Tuberculosis (TB) skin test services vary across BC and may be available through a local health unit, doctors' office, pharmacy or travel health clinic. Many people have to pay for the TB skin test, as they are not eligible for the publicly-funded (free) TB skin test. Find a health unit near you and ask about TB skin tests in your area here.
